title: For Sale/Trade:  WWII Finnish Tikka M31 Suomi
postcontent: For sale or trade is a TNW import Tikka Finnish Suomi m31 with 5 original, SA marked 36 rd stick magazines and carry case. The Suomi was originally the main submachine gun used by the Finnish forces in the Winter War of 1939-1940 and the Continuation War, as well as other forces during and after WWII, and was the basis for the later Russian PPSH-41 design. Barrel is orignal Finnish barrel with mandatory extension welded on by importer (TNW) to comply with SBR restrictions. Receiver is made in USA I believe to comply with 922r, but all other parts are original Finn. The carbine shoots great and has a slightly improved trigger than most of the rebuilds/imports floating around. Seriously a fun gun to shoot (just read reviews) with tight shot group, but I've got a couple other things I'm really wanting to put in the collecton right not. These are getting hard to find, as they are no longer produced or imported. Yes, it is heavy, as this once SMG was made for real men in the 1930s and needed to be able to function properly in freezing temperatures and stand up to the elements of war.
